n and Citra and Rowen get separated and are training under different scythes. Citra is under Honorable Scythe Curie and Rowen gets the evil Scythe Goddard &lt;--- I'm not even calling him honorable. He's a twat! <br><br>There is a lot more going on in the book and reasons for this that and the other but you can read all of that for yourself. <br><br>For me, the book was awesome and that's all I care about. And that ending . . . <br><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1481036882ra/21377543.gif" alt=" " class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br><br>YES, JUST YES!!!! ♥<br><br>MY BLOG: <a href="http://melissa413readsalot.blogspot.com/2016/12/scythe-by-neal-shusterman.html" rel="nofollow noopener">Melissa Martin's Reading List</a></span>
