<span id="freeTextContainer7888133624092366866">4.5 stars <br/><br/>TW: suicide; death of children <br/><br/>While there were a few things that felt a little two dimensional, I overall really enjoyed this discussion of a utopian future that uses ordained “reapers” as the only means to death in society and what that means for both society and the people in this organization. There were a number of twists I didn’t see coming, and it even ended in a way that it could be read as a stand-alone, which I appreciate. </span>

