    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2483837216" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2483837216" />
    <a title="Angelica" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/16201093-angelica"><img alt="Angelica" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1507050077p2/16201093.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2483837216?book_show_action=true">Aug 05, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Angelica" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Angelica" href="/user/show/16201093-angelica">Angelica</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16201093-angelica?shelf=release-2017">release-2017</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16201093-angelica?shelf=read-2018">read-2018</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16201093-angelica?shelf=cool-tittle">cool-tittle</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16201093-angelica?shelf=reviewed">reviewed</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16201093-angelica?shelf=four-star">four-star</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16201093-angelica?shelf=funny">funny</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16201093-angelica?shelf=action">action</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2483837216" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5729460063164474851"><b>How dare this book mess with my fragile emotions!?!<br/><br/>I was so stressed while reading this book! UGH! This sequel is going to kill me and you are all invited to my funeral. </b><br/><br/>When I first picked up this book, I must admit, I didn&apos;t like it.<br/><br/>The premise was interesting and the writing was fine. I just didn&apos;t care for it. I read the first 90 or so pages and almost gave up. Then I decided to use one of my Audible credits and listening to the audiobook. I started it from the beginning and let myself get t</span>
  <span id="freeText5729460063164474851" style="display:none"><b>How dare this book mess with my fragile emotions!?!<br /><br />I was so stressed while reading this book! UGH! This sequel is going to kill me and you are all invited to my funeral. </b><br /><br />When I first picked up this book, I must admit, I didn't like it.<br /><br />The premise was interesting and the writing was fine. I just didn't care for it. I read the first 90 or so pages and almost gave up. Then I decided to use one of my Audible credits and listening to the audiobook. I started it from the beginning and let myself get taken in by the story. I thought I was going to be able to relax while I listened, or casually do some chores.<br /><br /><b>I was wrong!</b><br /><br />This book stressed me. I was at the edge of my seat the entire time! At one point I was washing the dishes as I listened and I honestly stood in place, holding the same plate for like ten minutes because I got so into the story!<br /><br />There were also parts that I listened to while also reading along with the book in hand and I just couldn't stop! I would tell myself that I'd only read one more chapter and before I knew it two hours of my life were gone! UGH!<br /><br />Ok, so this book is about a world where mankind no longer dies. In order to keep the population size in line, a select group of people is selected as Scythes, the only people with the authority to cause permanent death. These Scythes are trained and sent out into the world and told to kill at their discretion. Some of these Scythes are honorable, aware of the burden and necessity of their profession. Others are ruthless, disregarding the core values of the Scythedom and taking pleasure from the lives they take. Then there are our two main characters, Citra and Rowan, Scythe's apprentices who hold both the potential for goodness and darkness in their hearts.<br /><br />Through them we get to explore the interesting utopia that Shusterman has created, as well as dive into many moral debated on what it means to be human, and if we can be truly considered human now that we do not face the consequence of death. <b>Honestly, it was all fantastically written.</b> I love the idea of the Scythes, and especially that of the Thunderhead, watching over them.<br /><br /><b>So, why not the whole five stars? Well, this book actually had a lot of problems.</b><br /><br />First is the romance. <b>This book is strange in the way that romance is both a nonintrusive and yet critical part of the story.</b> This book doesn't show much romance between the two MC's, which is good. But, their supposed 'love' for each other is one of their main motivators, which is bad. <b>Having a romance that is both lacking and integral to the plot, just doesn't work.</b><br /><b>Also, there were points in the book that were there only as conflict for the sake of conflict.</b> One of the main plot points is that Citra and Rowan are set up against each other for the position of Scythe, then the stakes are raised to say that the loser will die. And this is done for no reason. It makes no sense that one should die, and they even point it out! All of this could have been avoided!<br /><br /><b>Lastly, this book is actually kind of slow</b>. Had I not listened to the audiobook, I don't think I would have enjoyed it as much. Once the plot gets going, it's actually really interesting, but it does take it a minute to really start. So, keep that in mind if you want to read this.<br /><br /><b>In the end, do I recommend this? Heck yeah! </b>I really enjoyed it and can't wait to read the sequel, Thunderhead, next month. If the cons I described aren't things that would bother you, then I definitely think you should add this to your TBR. Also, I highly recommend this as an audiobook. Trust me, it was awesome and it won't disappoint!<br /><br /><br />Follow Me Here Too:<b> <a href="http://www.thebookcovergirls.wordpress.com" rel="nofollow noopener">My Blog</a> || <a href="https://twitter.com/covergirlreads" rel="nofollow noopener">Twitter</a> || <a href="https://www.bloglovin.com/blogs/book-cover-girl-19339391" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">Bloglovin'</a> || <a href="https://www.instagram.com/thebookcovergirls//" rel="nofollow noopener">Instagram</a> || <a href="https://thebookcovergirls.tumblr.com/" rel="nofollow noopener">Tumblr</a> || <a href="https://www.pinterest.com/thebookcovergirls/" rel="nofollow noopener">Pinterest</a></b></span>
  <a data-text-id="5729460063164474851" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


